      "body": "I made some [miri_println stuff](https://github.com/KMiri-rs/asterinas/commit/7f6e0d086ae15089e3f644ef022e573ddf7876f3). The problem is self and cpu_local_start are physical addresses, but sometimes are virtual addresses. `base + offset` just overflows. The aftermath of https://github.com/KMiri-rs/KMiri/issues/31.\n```\noffset=0x32 self=0x400032 cpu_local_start=0x400000\nptr=0xffffffff80400032 base=0xffffffff80400000 offset=0x32\n[alloc_child] early_alloc\nframe_paddr=0x1200000 vaddr=0xffff800001200000 PAGE_SIZE=4096\n[alloc_child] early_alloc\nframe_paddr=0x1201000 vaddr=0xffff800001201000 PAGE_SIZE=4096\n[alloc_child] early_alloc\nframe_paddr=0x1202000 vaddr=0xffff800001202000 PAGE_SIZE=4096\noffset=0xffffffff80000020 self=0xffffffff80400020 cpu_local_start=0x400000\nbase=0xffffffff80400000 offset=0xffffffff80000020\n```\n\n```\n        let ptr = (base + offset) as *const Self;\n```\n\n",
      "author_association": "MEMBER",
